 Susie Clark , of Evening Shade , found the 3.69-carat white diamond in a 37.5-acre search field on Thursday , her last day of a trip to the park .
Clark named the pinto-bean-sized , teardrop-shaped gem a ` hallelujah diamond ' because she spotted the gem .
Clark plans to keep the teard-sized diamond , which is the largest diamond in the park this year .